17 (3) Nothing in this section prohibits a county from regulating short-term rentals as defined in 15-68-
18 101.
19 (4) A county may require a fee for reviewing applications to create accessory dwelling units. The
20 one-time application fee may be up to $250 for each accessory dwelling unit. Nothing in this section prohibits a
21 county from requiring its usual building fees in addition to the application fee.
22 (5) A county that has not adopted or amended regulations pursuant to this section by [the effective
23 date of this act] shall review and permit accessory dwelling units in accordance with the requirements of this
24 section until regulations are adopted or amended. Regulations in effect on or after [the effective date of this
25 act], that apply to accessory dwelling units and do not comply with this section are void.
26 (6) The provisions of this section do not supersede applicable building codes, fire codes, or public
27 health and safety regulations adopted pursuant to Title 50, chapter 2.
