12 (b) "by right" means the ability to be approved without requiring:
13 (i) a public hearing;
14 (ii) a variance, conditional use permit, special permit, or special exception; or
15 (iii) other discretionary zoning action other than a determination that a site plan conforms with
16 applicable zoning regulations;
17 (c) "county" means a county that exercises zoning powers under this part;
18 (d) "gross floor area" means the interior habitable area of a single-family dwelling or an accessory
19 dwelling unit; and
20 (e) "single-family dwelling" means a building with one or more rooms designed for residential living
21 purposes by one household that is detached from any other dwelling unit.
